{
  "texts": [
    "According to research, the world's population will increase to roughly 9.6 billion people by 2050.",
    "Hence, to feed the population in 2050, the Food & Agricultural Organization (FAO) predicts food production will need to rise by 70%, with double meat production in beef, poultry, and hog (Higa et al., 2021).",
    "Therefore, the demand for meat and seafood is speculated to rise with the rising of aquaculture business.",
    "Food manufacturers have been compelled to develop novel alternative protein-based products to muscle meat in response to consumer demand for sustainable food.",
    "The production of muscle meat Extended author information available on the last page of the article from livestock animals contributes to the deterioration of the ecosystem worldwide by consuming land (30%) and its water (8%) in addition to the gas emissions (14.5%) (over those from transportation) (Lamb et al., 2021; Siddiqui et al., 2022)."
  ]
}